explains our personality traits.

00:00:33.360 --> 00:00:35.120 align:middle line:84%
That said, today,
we're going to delve

00:00:35.120 --> 00:00:37.700 align:middle line:84%
into Vedic astrology,
the backbone of choosing

00:00:37.700 --> 00:00:41.220 align:middle line:84%
relationships, auspicious
times for business, and more,

00:00:41.220 --> 00:00:46.170 align:middle line:84%
with Brent Becvar, an Associate
of Deepak Chopra's for 33 years,

00:00:46.170 --> 00:00:46.980 align:middle line:90%
so welcome.

00:00:46.980 --> 00:00:49.790 align:middle line:84%
I'm so happy to have you here
and have this conversation

00:00:49.790 --> 00:00:53.270 align:middle line:84%
with you, because I
like a lot of people--

00:00:53.270 --> 00:00:56.420 align:middle line:84%
personally, because you go
on your personality traits,

00:00:56.420 --> 00:00:59.250 align:middle line:84%
and I say, I feel more
of the Vedic thing for me

00:00:59.250 --> 00:01:02.190 align:middle line:84%
than the other one,
all right, tropical.

00:01:02.190 --> 00:01:04.328 align:middle line:84%
But other people feel
the opposite way.

00:01:04.328 --> 00:01:06.120 align:middle line:84%
And we're going to get
into the differences

00:01:06.120 --> 00:01:08.475 align:middle line:90%
between the two and much more.

00:01:08.475 --> 00:01:10.600 align:middle line:84%
But first of all, we need
to get to know you a bit.

00:01:10.600 --> 00:01:13.300 align:middle line:84%
So they already heard me say
Deepak Chopra for 30 years.

00:01:13.300 --> 00:01:14.920 align:middle line:90%
But let's back up before that.

00:01:14.920 --> 00:01:16.305 align:middle line:90%
So you were a psychotherapist?

00:01:16.305 --> 00:01:17.403 align:middle line:90%
>> BRENT BECVAR: Yes.

00:01:17.403 --> 00:01:19.320 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Let's talk
about that a little bit,

00:01:19.320 --> 00:01:22.830 align:middle line:84%
and how that started feeding
into any kind of usefulness

00:01:22.830 --> 00:01:25.566 align:middle line:84%
in this profession
now as an astrologer.

00:01:25.566 --> 00:01:28.290 align:middle line:10%
>> BECVAR: I think I've always
been interested in going

00:01:28.290 --> 00:01:30.370 align:middle line:10%
into the mystery
to find the truth.

00:01:30.370 --> 00:01:32.130 align:middle line:10%
I think I can see
that as something

00:01:32.130 --> 00:01:33.910 align:middle line:10%
consistent throughout my life.

00:01:33.910 --> 00:01:37.530 align:middle line:84%
I was always interested
in going into the mystery.

00:01:37.530 --> 00:01:40.468 align:middle line:10%
And I was actually
interested in astrology

00:01:40.468 --> 00:01:42.010 align:middle line:10%
before I knew there
was such a thing.

00:01:42.010 --> 00:01:43.560 align:middle line:10%
I would meet
someone, I would want

00:01:43.560 --> 00:01:45.660 align:middle line:10%
to know when they were born.

00:01:45.660 --> 00:01:48.940 align:middle line:10%
And I felt like I had some
sense, even as a child.

00:01:48.940 --> 00:01:51.440 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: You wanted to know
the birth date, even as a kid?

00:01:51.440 --> 00:01:53.732 align:middle line:84%
Like it was giving you some
kind of hidden information.

00:01:53.732 --> 00:01:54.540 align:middle line:90%
>> BECVAR: Yeah.

00:01:54.540 --> 00:01:55.440 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Interesting.

00:01:55.440 --> 00:01:56.648 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, you're born to do that.

00:01:56.648 --> 00:01:58.080 align:middle line:90%
>> BECVAR: I can't explain it.

00:01:58.080 --> 00:02:00.640 align:middle line:84%
During the course of my life,
I've lived here in Boulder,

00:02:00.640 --> 00:02:01.440 align:middle line:90%
actually.

00:02:01.440 --> 00:02:04.360 align:middle line:90%
I was at CU as a student.

00:02:04.360 --> 00:02:07.540 align:middle line:84%
And I got very
interested in yoga.

00:02:07.540 --> 00:02:09.930 align:middle line:84%
At that time, I was
about 20 years old.

00:02:09.930 --> 00:02:14.160 align:middle line:84%
And I became a yoga teacher
with Swami Satchidananda.

00:02:14.160 --> 00:02:16.920 align:middle line:84%
Integral Yoga
Institute was here.

00:02:16.920 --> 00:02:20.640 align:middle line:84%
And I began to explore
the Vedic tradition

00:02:20.640 --> 00:02:23.820 align:middle line:90%
from that time in my life.

00:02:23.820 --> 00:02:28.380 align:middle line:84%
I then did get my
masters in psychology

00:02:28.380 --> 00:02:31.030 align:middle line:84%
and began working in
traditional psychotherapy.

00:02:31.030 --> 00:02:34.380 align:middle line:84%
But I didn't find it
very satisfying for me.

00:02:34.380 --> 00:02:36.790 align:middle line:90%
I focused on gestalt therapy.

00:02:36.790 --> 00:02:40.530 align:middle line:84%
That was the mentor that
I had in graduate school.

00:02:40.530 --> 00:02:42.520 align:middle line:84%
But I was always
interested in yoga,

00:02:42.520 --> 00:02:45.060 align:middle line:84%
and I always felt like I
wanted to somehow marry

00:02:45.060 --> 00:02:49.360 align:middle line:84%
the Vedic tradition with
psychotherapy or with therapy.

00:02:49.360 --> 00:02:51.790 align:middle line:84%
It's a longer story
how I met Deepak,

00:02:51.790 --> 00:02:53.752 align:middle line:90%
but I did begin to explore.

00:02:53.752 --> 00:02:56.210 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Wasn't there a little
detour along the way, too,

00:02:56.210 --> 00:02:56.670 align:middle line:90%
in advertising?

00:02:56.670 --> 00:02:57.610 align:middle line:90%
>> BECVAR: I did, yes.

00:02:57.610 --> 00:02:58.670 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Yeah,
let's talk about that.

00:02:58.670 --> 00:03:01.045 align:middle line:84%
Because I mean, it all kind
of comes together in the end.

00:03:01.045 --> 00:03:03.830 align:middle line:84%
>> BECVAR: Well, it was actually
a good transition for me

00:03:03.830 --> 00:03:04.630 align:middle line:90%
at the time after.

00:03:04.630 --> 00:03:09.190 align:middle line:84%
I got a little disenchanted with
psychotherapy after a few years.

00:03:09.190 --> 00:03:11.830 align:middle line:84%
So I took a break
and I got into--

00:03:11.830 --> 00:03:15.880 align:middle line:84%
I took a vocational
preference test.

00:03:15.880 --> 00:03:18.110 align:middle line:84%
Then I used to give to
my clients at times,

00:03:18.110 --> 00:03:21.610 align:middle line:84%
and I had a very high score in
advertising, which was something

00:03:21.610 --> 00:03:23.390 align:middle line:90%
I was surprised about.

00:03:23.390 --> 00:03:25.360 align:middle line:90%
And I thought, that sounds fun.

00:03:25.360 --> 00:03:27.650 align:middle line:84%
I loved media, I
loved television.

00:03:27.650 --> 00:03:32.320 align:middle line:84%
And through some contacts
of my father's, I

00:03:32.320 --> 00:03:34.630 align:middle line:84%
got into a television
station and began

00:03:34.630 --> 00:03:35.875 align:middle line:90%
working in advertising.

00:03:35.875 --> 00:03:36.675 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Where?

00:03:36.675 --> 00:03:40.142 align:middle line:84%
>> BECVAR: At that time,
in Louisville, Kentucky.

00:03:40.142 --> 00:03:43.540 align:middle line:84%
And I began writing commercials,
and directing commercials,

00:03:43.540 --> 00:03:45.050 align:middle line:90%
and also I had clients.

00:03:45.050 --> 00:03:46.250 align:middle line:90%
And it was really fun.

00:03:46.250 --> 00:03:47.710 align:middle line:90%
I learned a lot.

00:03:47.710 --> 00:03:50.200 align:middle line:84%
I learned a lot about
many different businesses

00:03:50.200 --> 00:03:51.830 align:middle line:84%
and many different
kinds of people.

00:03:51.830 --> 00:03:53.930 align:middle line:90%
I was a bit shy before that.

00:03:53.930 --> 00:03:57.090 align:middle line:84%
So it was a good 10,
11 years in my life.

00:03:57.090 --> 00:04:00.020 align:middle line:84%
But then I came to a
point where I really

00:04:00.020 --> 00:04:03.470 align:middle line:84%
didn't feel that I
was doing anything

00:04:03.470 --> 00:04:05.460 align:middle line:90%
of real importance for me.

00:04:05.460 --> 00:04:07.220 align:middle line:84%
Nothing wrong with
advertising, but I

00:04:07.220 --> 00:04:11.780 align:middle line:84%
didn't feel like I was really
in alignment with my nature.

00:04:11.780 --> 00:04:15.200 align:middle line:84%
And I talk a lot about
this with my clients

00:04:15.200 --> 00:04:21.529 align:middle line:84%
because we all have a dharma,
a purpose, you might say.

00:04:21.529 --> 00:04:24.000 align:middle line:84%
And when we're in
alignment with our nature,

00:04:24.000 --> 00:04:27.090 align:middle line:84%
we feel fulfilled just
in doing that thing,

00:04:27.090 --> 00:04:29.150 align:middle line:84%
much as I'm sure you
do in doing the work

00:04:29.150 --> 00:04:30.930 align:middle line:84%
you've been doing
all these many years.

00:04:30.930 --> 00:04:32.480 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: I found out this
morning that you had seen

00:04:32.480 --> 00:04:33.030 align:middle line:90%
my chart.

00:04:33.030 --> 00:04:33.850 align:middle line:90%
You have seen my chart.

00:04:33.850 --> 00:04:34.650 align:middle line:90%
>> BECVAR: I did.

00:04:34.650 --> 00:04:37.680 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And you said that I'm
right where I'm supposed to be,

00:04:37.680 --> 00:04:38.480 align:middle line:90%
dharma-wise.

00:04:38.480 --> 00:04:40.800 align:middle line:84%
>> BECVAR: Absolutely,
absolutely.

00:04:40.800 --> 00:04:45.180 align:middle line:84%
And you're doing a
great service to others.

00:04:45.180 --> 00:04:50.360 align:middle line:84%
You're playing your part
in this big play we're in.

00:04:50.360 --> 00:04:52.440 align:middle line:84%
So it is important
that we really

00:04:52.440 --> 00:04:54.370 align:middle line:84%
try to find out what
we're meant to do,

00:04:54.370 --> 00:04:55.690 align:middle line:90%
because we all have a purpose.

00:04:55.690 --> 00:04:58.080 align:middle line:84%
We all have something
that we can contribute.

00:04:58.080 --> 00:05:03.190 align:middle line:84%
And when we do, we feel
exalted in doing that thing.

00:05:03.190 --> 00:05:04.690 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Well,
it's so fulfilling.

00:05:04.690 --> 00:05:05.970 align:middle line:90%
It takes a lot of--

00:05:05.970 --> 00:05:09.030 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I find I don't
have a lot of the anxieties

00:05:09.030 --> 00:05:12.300 align:middle line:84%
that people tend
to have in my life

00:05:12.300 --> 00:05:16.510 align:middle line:84%
because I connected with my
dharma so early on in life.

00:05:16.510 --> 00:05:19.770 align:middle line:84%
And so I didn't really
question, why am I here?

00:05:19.770 --> 00:05:20.830 align:middle line:90%
Should I be doing this?

00:05:20.830 --> 00:05:22.330 align:middle line:84%
I don't have any
of those questions.

00:05:22.330 --> 00:05:23.510 align:middle line:90%
I just kept proceeding forward.

00:05:23.510 --> 00:05:24.960 align:middle line:84%
>> BECVAR: You were really
lucky and fortunate.

00:05:24.960 --> 00:05:25.280 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: I was very lucky.

00:05:25.280 --> 00:05:28.200 align:middle line:84%
>> BECVAR: And it shows in
your chart because of the--

00:05:28.200 --> 00:05:30.120 align:middle line:84%
I told you, the ruler
of your ascendant

00:05:30.120 --> 00:05:32.380 align:middle line:84%
is in the ninth house,
the house of dharma.

00:05:32.380 --> 00:05:35.470 align:middle line:84%
And it gives this sort of
lifelong pursuit of knowledge

00:05:35.470 --> 00:05:36.270 align:middle line:90%
as well.

00:05:36.270 --> 00:05:37.070 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yes.

00:05:37.070 --> 00:05:40.740 align:middle line:84%
>> BECVAR: When we're in
alignment with dharma,

00:05:40.740 --> 00:05:44.237 align:middle line:84%
we don't have that empty
feeling like I need something,

00:05:44.237 --> 00:05:45.070 align:middle line:90%
something's missing.

00:05:45.070 --> 00:05:45.385 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Exactly, yeah.

00:05:45.385 --> 00:05:46.385 align:middle line:90%
>> BECVAR: And I think--

00:05:46.385 --> 00:05:49.030 align:middle line:84%
I do talk about this
subject with my clients.

00:05:49.030 --> 00:05:51.360 align:middle line:84%
There's a beautiful
body of knowledge

00:05:51.360 --> 00:05:53.710 align:middle line:84%
from the Vedic tradition
called the Purusharthas,

00:05:53.710 --> 00:05:54.627 align:middle line:90%
the four aims of life.

00:05:54.627 --> 00:05:56.335 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: We're going
to get into those.

00:05:56.335 --> 00:05:58.260 align:middle line:84%
But let's find out how
you finally discovered

00:05:58.260 --> 00:06:01.300 align:middle line:84%
your own dharma after you were
dissatisfied with advertising.

00:06:01.300 --> 00:06:04.967 align:middle line:84%
>> BECVAR: About that time, I
was starting to feel like, OK,

00:06:04.967 --> 00:06:05.800 align:middle line:90%
something's missing.

00:06:05.800 --> 00:06:09.250 align:middle line:84%
And I really began
to pray sincerely.

00:06:09.250 --> 00:06:11.650 align:middle line:84%
And something shifted in my
heart when that happened.

00:06:11.650 --> 00:06:14.670 align:middle line:84%
And shortly after that,
through an interesting set

00:06:14.670 --> 00:06:18.065 align:middle line:84%
of circumstances, I met
Dr. Chopra, Deepak Chopra.

00:06:18.065 --> 00:06:19.370 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: That's a big leap.

00:06:19.370 --> 00:06:22.870 align:middle line:84%
>> BECVAR: It was one of the
greatest gifts in my life,

00:06:22.870 --> 00:06:24.330 align:middle line:90%
I'll tell you.

00:06:24.330 --> 00:06:27.730 align:middle line:84%
He's been a great friend and
mentor over these many 33 years.

00:06:27.730 --> 00:06:33.420 align:middle line:84%
But through a remarkable
series of coincidences

00:06:33.420 --> 00:06:37.260 align:middle line:84%
and synchronicities and good
fortune and karma, I guess,

00:06:37.260 --> 00:06:41.340 align:middle line:84%
I was invited to come and work
for him up in Massachusetts.

00:06:41.340 --> 00:06:45.690 align:middle line:84%
And as an administrator
there, that

00:06:45.690 --> 00:06:47.950 align:middle line:84%
began, as I said,
33 years ago, but it

00:06:47.950 --> 00:06:49.780 align:middle line:84%
was right at the
beginning of that time

00:06:49.780 --> 00:06:51.800 align:middle line:90%
that I met a Vedic astrologer.

00:06:51.800 --> 00:06:53.600 align:middle line:84%
And I'd been interested
in astrology,

00:06:53.600 --> 00:06:55.240 align:middle line:90%
as I said, since I was little.

00:06:55.240 --> 00:06:57.930 align:middle line:84%
Even studied Western
astrology for 20 years.

00:06:57.930 --> 00:06:58.730 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yeah.

00:06:58.730 --> 00:07:01.850 align:middle line:84%
>> BECVAR: So I knew there
was something to astrology.

00:07:01.850 --> 00:07:06.160 align:middle line:84%
And I have compassion
for people that

00:07:06.160 --> 00:07:09.520 align:middle line:84%
are attached to
their Western chart

00:07:09.520 --> 00:07:13.780 align:middle line:84%
because I think we know there's
some truth that can be found

00:07:13.780 --> 00:07:15.790 align:middle line:90%
in this knowledge of astrology.

00:07:15.790 --> 00:07:21.820 align:middle line:84%
Every exalted wisdom tradition,
every culture, exalted culture,

00:07:21.820 --> 00:07:26.510 align:middle line:84%
has had a very high knowledge
of astrology/astronomy.

00:07:26.510 --> 00:07:29.170 align:middle line:84%
It was one thing,
astrology/astronomy.

00:07:29.170 --> 00:07:33.070 align:middle line:84%
So I think we sense that we're
not separate from this greater

00:07:33.070 --> 00:07:35.200 align:middle line:84%
body of the universe, and
there's something for us

00:07:35.200 --> 00:07:38.660 align:middle line:84%
to learn in the same way that
we're connected to the cycles,

00:07:38.660 --> 00:07:44.630 align:middle line:84%
the sidereal, the circadian
rhythm of day and night.

00:07:44.630 --> 00:07:47.688 align:middle line:84%
The lunar rhythms, of course,
we're intimately connected.

00:07:47.688 --> 00:07:49.980 align:middle line:84%
And everything in nature is
connected to these rhythms.

00:07:49.980 --> 00:07:52.620 align:middle line:84%
The seasonal rhythms, and
these greater rhythms,

00:07:52.620 --> 00:07:54.980 align:middle line:84%
these planetary
rhythms are very much

00:07:54.980 --> 00:07:57.150 align:middle line:90%
a part of our bigger awareness.

00:07:57.150 --> 00:08:00.480 align:middle line:84%
Maybe not all the time of
our conscious awareness,

00:08:00.480 --> 00:08:04.020 align:middle line:84%
but our super conscious
awareness, let's say.

00:08:04.020 --> 00:08:06.150 align:middle line:84%
I kept studying
Western astrology.

00:08:06.150 --> 00:08:08.160 align:middle line:84%
I often say it was like
an article of clothing

00:08:08.160 --> 00:08:09.300 align:middle line:90%
I wanted to squeeze into.

00:08:09.300 --> 00:08:12.780 align:middle line:84%
I wanted to wear it, but
it didn't quite fit for me.

00:08:12.780 --> 00:08:15.180 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: So you weren't--
like I said in the open,

00:08:15.180 --> 00:08:17.790 align:middle line:84%
you weren't even on
a personal level,

00:08:17.790 --> 00:08:21.080 align:middle line:84%
particularly identifying with
what was assigned to you via

00:08:21.080 --> 00:08:22.460 align:middle line:90%
Western astrology, I take it.

00:08:22.460 --> 00:08:24.650 align:middle line:84%
You felt there was
something that needed

00:08:24.650 --> 00:08:25.950 align:middle line:90%
to shift in that for you?

00:08:25.950 --> 00:08:30.200 align:middle line:84%
>> BECVAR: Yeah, I mean,
like a lot of people that are

00:08:30.200 --> 00:08:33.740 align:middle line:84%
interested in Western astrology,
I kind of align myself with

00:08:33.740 --> 00:08:39.080 align:middle line:84%
those planetary positions,
the rising sign, the sun sign,

00:08:39.080 --> 00:08:41.929 align:middle line:84%
and all the other
planetary positions.

00:08:41.929 --> 00:08:46.130 align:middle line:84%
But somehow, it just didn't
quite fit, as I said.

00:08:46.130 --> 00:08:50.060 align:middle line:84%
And when I met this
Vedic astrologer,

00:08:50.060 --> 00:08:56.220 align:middle line:84%
this was an important moment in
my life because he did my chart.

00:08:56.220 --> 00:09:00.710 align:middle line:84%
And for the first time in my
life, I felt that that suit fit.

00:09:00.710 --> 00:09:02.240 align:middle line:84%
It was exactly
because everything

00:09:02.240 --> 00:09:05.150 align:middle line:84%
is different in a Vedic
chart by 24 degrees

00:09:05.150 --> 00:09:06.925 align:middle line:90%
from a Western tropical chart.

00:09:06.925 --> 00:09:10.790 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: So it almost slides
everything three weeks forward

00:09:10.790 --> 00:09:12.080 align:middle line:90%
or backward.

00:09:12.080 --> 00:09:16.580 align:middle line:84%
So for example, in my chart,
I would be a Scorpio somewhere

00:09:16.580 --> 00:09:18.870 align:middle line:90%
around the November 14 area.

00:09:18.870 --> 00:09:19.880 align:middle line:90%
So in everything seems--

00:09:19.880 --> 00:09:20.510 align:middle line:90%
>> BECVAR: Happy birthday.

00:09:20.510 --> 00:09:21.500 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Thank you.

