>> BECVAR: Everything in the
horoscope moves 24 degrees.

00:09:33.960 --> 00:09:34.070 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yeah.

00:09:34.070 --> 00:09:36.070 align:middle line:84%
>> BECVAR: But most
especially, the rising sign,

00:09:36.070 --> 00:09:39.170 align:middle line:84%
because we don't think of you in
terms of your sun sign as much

00:09:39.170 --> 00:09:41.280 align:middle line:84%
in the Vedic chart
as your rising sign.

00:09:41.280 --> 00:09:45.330 align:middle line:84%
The rising sign is just as
we're turning with the planet

00:09:45.330 --> 00:09:47.880 align:middle line:90%
as we are right now.

00:09:47.880 --> 00:09:51.580 align:middle line:84%
And as the sun appeared to rise
this morning, it wasn't rising,

00:09:51.580 --> 00:09:53.320 align:middle line:84%
we were just turning
in relation to it.

00:09:53.320 --> 00:09:55.420 align:middle line:84%
In the same way, as we
turn with the planet,

00:09:55.420 --> 00:09:58.890 align:middle line:84%
different constellations will
appear on the Eastern horizon

00:09:58.890 --> 00:10:00.790 align:middle line:84%
at different times
of the day and night.

00:10:00.790 --> 00:10:03.390 align:middle line:84%
And they change about
every hour to two hours.

00:10:03.390 --> 00:10:07.620 align:middle line:84%
So that really sets
up the relationship

00:10:07.620 --> 00:10:10.202 align:middle line:84%
of all, the relationship
of the planets

00:10:10.202 --> 00:10:12.410 align:middle line:84%
at the time of a person's
birth to the event of the--

00:10:12.410 --> 00:10:14.460 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: So the rising sun
takes precedence over the sun

00:10:14.460 --> 00:10:15.545 align:middle line:90%
sign in Vedic astrology?

00:10:15.545 --> 00:10:16.775 align:middle line:90%
>> BECVAR: Yes, it does.

00:10:16.775 --> 00:10:18.400 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, it's the first
thing to consider,

00:10:18.400 --> 00:10:24.300 align:middle line:84%
because then you see how all the
other planetary positions relate

00:10:24.300 --> 00:10:26.610 align:middle line:90%
to that moment of birth.

00:10:26.610 --> 00:10:29.910 align:middle line:84%
And the rising sun
does give a lot of--

00:10:29.910 --> 00:10:32.620 align:middle line:84%
has a lot to do with the
personality, the physical body,

00:10:32.620 --> 00:10:36.120 align:middle line:84%
the way we present ourselves to
the world and a lot of the way

00:10:36.120 --> 00:10:39.060 align:middle line:84%
we're perceived
by others as well.

00:10:39.060 --> 00:10:43.160 align:middle line:84%
The moon position is
also very important,

00:10:43.160 --> 00:10:46.250 align:middle line:84%
and the moon has a lot
to do with the manas,

00:10:46.250 --> 00:10:48.500 align:middle line:84%
the intuitive mind,
the subtle mind.

00:10:48.500 --> 00:10:50.540 align:middle line:84%
I think of it as
being that aspect,

00:10:50.540 --> 00:10:54.460 align:middle line:84%
that very sensitive aspect of
ourselves which is constantly

00:10:54.460 --> 00:10:55.430 align:middle line:90%
discerning.

00:10:55.430 --> 00:10:57.130 align:middle line:84%
Is this a nourishing
impression that's

00:10:57.130 --> 00:10:58.960 align:middle line:84%
coming in through
the five senses

00:10:58.960 --> 00:11:00.650 align:middle line:90%
from the environment for me?

00:11:00.650 --> 00:11:02.060 align:middle line:90%
Or is it not nourishing?

00:11:02.060 --> 00:11:06.020 align:middle line:84%
So we're always a little-- and
that's our intuition, really.

00:11:06.020 --> 00:11:08.030 align:middle line:84%
And our sixth sense,
we're always--

00:11:08.030 --> 00:11:09.680 align:middle line:84%
is this a nourishing--
is this safe?

00:11:09.680 --> 00:11:12.320 align:middle line:84%
Is this something I want
to take in or is it not?

00:11:12.320 --> 00:11:15.000 align:middle line:84%
So the moon is very
important because the moon

00:11:15.000 --> 00:11:17.500 align:middle line:84%
and where the mind goes, that's
kind of where the rest of us

00:11:17.500 --> 00:11:18.300 align:middle line:90%
goes.

00:11:18.300 --> 00:11:20.950 align:middle line:84%
And in the state of
the mind determines

00:11:20.950 --> 00:11:25.880 align:middle line:84%
how much joy we take in our
experience moment to moment,

00:11:25.880 --> 00:11:28.600 align:middle line:84%
or if we're just on
guard all the time,

00:11:28.600 --> 00:11:31.300 align:middle line:84%
the sympathetic nervous
system as opposed

00:11:31.300 --> 00:11:33.040 align:middle line:84%
to the parasympathetic
nervous system.

00:11:33.040 --> 00:11:35.990 align:middle line:84%
So the moon is very important
part of the horoscope.

00:11:35.990 --> 00:11:40.120 align:middle line:84%
Also, in the Vedic
chart, the planet

00:11:40.120 --> 00:11:43.070 align:middle line:84%
that rules your rising sign
is also very important.

00:11:43.070 --> 00:11:46.000 align:middle line:84%
And each of the
12 ascendants has

00:11:46.000 --> 00:11:51.070 align:middle line:84%
one planet that presents the
qualities of that rising sign.

00:11:51.070 --> 00:11:54.490 align:middle line:84%
People that are ruled
by Venus, Taurus, rising

00:11:54.490 --> 00:11:56.350 align:middle line:84%
in the Vedic system,
and Libra rising

00:11:56.350 --> 00:11:58.610 align:middle line:84%
are ruled by Venus
or more Venusian.

00:11:58.610 --> 00:12:02.720 align:middle line:84%
They're more relational,
they're interested in harmony,

00:12:02.720 --> 00:12:07.620 align:middle line:84%
often, interested in balance
and design and fairness.

00:12:07.620 --> 00:12:09.142 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: The
beauty of all kinds.

00:12:09.142 --> 00:12:10.600 align:middle line:84%
>> BECVAR: The
beauty of all kinds.

00:12:10.600 --> 00:12:11.830 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Harmony
and beauty, yeah.

00:12:11.830 --> 00:12:13.540 align:middle line:84%
>> BECVAR: Harmony
and beauty, exactly.

00:12:13.540 --> 00:12:17.600 align:middle line:84%
And as I said, you've got a
prominent Venus in your chart.

00:12:17.600 --> 00:12:19.910 align:middle line:84%
People that are ruled
by Mars, however,

00:12:19.910 --> 00:12:21.680 align:middle line:90%
can have a lot of drive.

00:12:21.680 --> 00:12:26.620 align:middle line:84%
Mars is that planet of courage,
passion, energy, which we like

00:12:26.620 --> 00:12:29.210 align:middle line:84%
and it can make a
person a self-starter.

00:12:29.210 --> 00:12:31.598 align:middle line:84%
It can make them a
good athlete or--

00:12:31.598 --> 00:12:32.515 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Rebellious.

00:12:32.515 --> 00:12:35.540 align:middle line:84%
>> BECVAR: Warrior or
rebellious, yeah, of course.

00:12:35.540 --> 00:12:38.040 align:middle line:84%
But there's the shadow
side of every planet.

00:12:38.040 --> 00:12:39.780 align:middle line:84%
So you can give
irritability, anger,

00:12:39.780 --> 00:12:44.570 align:middle line:84%
impatience at times,
inflammatory disorders.

00:12:44.570 --> 00:12:48.980 align:middle line:84%
Mercurial people, Gemini
rising and Virgo rising people

00:12:48.980 --> 00:12:50.550 align:middle line:90%
are ruled by Mercury.

00:12:50.550 --> 00:12:53.390 align:middle line:84%
So Mercury, planet
of the intellect,

00:12:53.390 --> 00:12:56.510 align:middle line:90%
planet of communications a lot.

00:12:56.510 --> 00:13:00.120 align:middle line:84%
And Sagittarius is
ruled by Jupiter.

00:13:00.120 --> 00:13:04.700 align:middle line:84%
And Pisces is ruled by Jupiter,
Capricorn by Saturn and Aquarius

00:13:04.700 --> 00:13:06.960 align:middle line:90%
by Saturn in the Vedic system.

00:13:06.960 --> 00:13:09.320 align:middle line:84%
We don't use the
outer Saturan planets

00:13:09.320 --> 00:13:10.725 align:middle line:90%
of Uranus, Pluto, Neptune.

00:13:10.725 --> 00:13:11.870 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Oh, not at all?

00:13:11.870 --> 00:13:12.450 align:middle line:90%
>> BECVAR: Not at all.

00:13:12.450 --> 00:13:12.750 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Oh, interesting.

00:13:12.750 --> 00:13:15.510 align:middle line:84%
>> BECVAR: I mean, many Vedic
astrologers will include them.

00:13:15.510 --> 00:13:17.700 align:middle line:84%
I do include them
when I do a chart.

00:13:17.700 --> 00:13:21.590 align:middle line:84%
But traditional Vedic
astrology utilizes

00:13:21.590 --> 00:13:24.390 align:middle line:84%
what are called the true
planets, the visible planets.

00:13:24.390 --> 00:13:28.670 align:middle line:84%
And the system is very elegant
if you look at a Vedic chart.

00:13:28.670 --> 00:13:33.800 align:middle line:84%
Because Cancer and Leo are
right together, sun and moon.

00:13:33.800 --> 00:13:37.350 align:middle line:84%
And then next you have the
mercury-ruled constellations

00:13:37.350 --> 00:13:39.220 align:middle line:90%
of Gemini and Virgo.

00:13:39.220 --> 00:13:42.250 align:middle line:84%
Then you have Libra and
Taurus ruled by Venus.

00:13:42.250 --> 00:13:45.100 align:middle line:84%
Then you have Aries and
Scorpio ruled by Mars.

00:13:45.100 --> 00:13:47.850 align:middle line:84%
Then Pisces, Sagittarius
ruled by Jupiter,

00:13:47.850 --> 00:13:51.420 align:middle line:84%
and Capricorn and Aquarius
ruled by Saturn, farthest

00:13:51.420 --> 00:13:52.530 align:middle line:90%
from the sun.

00:13:52.530 --> 00:13:56.530 align:middle line:84%
So honestly, in
doing a Vedic chart,

00:13:56.530 --> 00:13:59.730 align:middle line:84%
I don't really find I need
to use the outer Saturn

00:13:59.730 --> 00:14:03.285 align:middle line:84%
planets, although
they're certainly useful,

00:14:03.285 --> 00:14:04.085 align:middle line:90%
can be very useful.

00:14:04.085 --> 00:14:05.710 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Well, what
about the notion,

00:14:05.710 --> 00:14:10.000 align:middle line:84%
like the Age of Aquarius, that
happened on November 19, 2024,

00:14:10.000 --> 00:14:12.270 align:middle line:90%
in Western astrology?

00:14:12.270 --> 00:14:16.360 align:middle line:84%
What is the actual date of
entering that Aquarian period?

00:14:16.360 --> 00:14:18.370 align:middle line:90%
Although that's Pluto.

