If you don't recognize
Pluto, how does that all--

00:14:20.650 --> 00:14:23.220 align:middle line:84%
how does the Age of Aquarius
work in the Vedic chart, then?

00:14:23.220 --> 00:14:25.980 align:middle line:84%
>> BECVAR: The Age of Aquarius,
I think I started to say that

00:14:25.980 --> 00:14:29.190 align:middle line:84%
because of that wobble
in the spin of the Earth,

00:14:29.190 --> 00:14:35.350 align:middle line:84%
the point where the sun rises
every spring equinox is the way

00:14:35.350 --> 00:14:38.510 align:middle line:90%
we determine the planetary age.

00:14:38.510 --> 00:14:43.120 align:middle line:84%
So in Western
astrology, they say that

00:14:43.120 --> 00:14:45.720 align:middle line:90%
on April, March 15 to April--

00:14:45.720 --> 00:14:46.520 align:middle line:90%
what is it?

00:14:46.520 --> 00:14:51.050 align:middle line:90%
March 21 to April 21 is Aries.

00:14:51.050 --> 00:14:52.060 align:middle line:90%
If the sun is--

00:14:52.060 --> 00:14:54.680 align:middle line:84%
I mean, if you're born at that
time, the sun was in Aries.

00:14:54.680 --> 00:14:59.860 align:middle line:84%
Well, the sun hasn't risen in
Aries on those dates in over

00:14:59.860 --> 00:15:00.980 align:middle line:90%
1,800 years.

00:15:00.980 --> 00:15:02.530 align:middle line:90%
It's been precessing.

00:15:02.530 --> 00:15:04.480 align:middle line:84%
Because of that wobble,
it's been rising

00:15:04.480 --> 00:15:06.410 align:middle line:90%
in the constellation of Pisces.

00:15:06.410 --> 00:15:10.070 align:middle line:84%
And we've been in the Piscean
age as a result of this.

00:15:10.070 --> 00:15:14.787 align:middle line:84%
A planetary age, an astrological
age lasts about 2,150 years,

00:15:14.787 --> 00:15:15.620 align:middle line:90%
something like that.

00:15:15.620 --> 00:15:17.330 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: So when do we
scooch on over into Aquarius?

00:15:17.330 --> 00:15:19.010 align:middle line:84%
>> BECVAR: So we're not
quite scootched in just yet,

