And I love it.

00:17:24.217 --> 00:17:26.800 align:middle line:84%
>> BECVAR: Well, there's another
really important point I just

00:17:26.800 --> 00:17:29.150 align:middle line:84%
want to make about this
precession of the equinoxes,

00:17:29.150 --> 00:17:32.380 align:middle line:84%
because in the Vedic tradition,
there are these Yugas or these

00:17:32.380 --> 00:17:33.890 align:middle line:90%
great spans of time.

00:17:33.890 --> 00:17:37.510 align:middle line:84%
The whole cycle of precession
takes about 26,000 years

00:17:37.510 --> 00:17:40.510 align:middle line:84%
for that precessional movement
all the way through all

00:17:40.510 --> 00:17:42.460 align:middle line:90%
the constellations.

00:17:42.460 --> 00:17:46.300 align:middle line:84%
In the Vedic tradition, it said
that there is a declining period

00:17:46.300 --> 00:17:49.280 align:middle line:84%
of half of that, maybe
13,000 years or so.

00:17:49.280 --> 00:17:52.100 align:middle line:84%
When consciousness
becomes more and more dim,

00:17:52.100 --> 00:17:55.040 align:middle line:84%
we go from the Satya
Yuga, the golden age,

00:17:55.040 --> 00:17:59.600 align:middle line:84%
