00:28:14.540 --> 00:28:15.940 align:middle line:90%
so material things.

00:28:15.940 --> 00:28:19.880 align:middle line:84%
Kama, as in kama sutra,
which means pleasure.

00:28:19.880 --> 00:28:22.520 align:middle line:84%
When we have our basic
resources in place,

00:28:22.520 --> 00:28:24.140 align:middle line:90%
we want to expand our enjoyment.

00:28:24.140 --> 00:28:26.630 align:middle line:84%
We look for relationships
to share pleasure.

00:28:26.630 --> 00:28:30.410 align:middle line:84%
So karma is a lot about
our psychological values,

00:28:30.410 --> 00:28:33.470 align:middle line:84%
like artha is about
our economic values,

00:28:33.470 --> 00:28:35.330 align:middle line:84%
dharma is about
our moral values.

00:28:35.330 --> 00:28:38.600 align:middle line:84%
And the fourth is moksha,
liberation, self-realization,

00:28:38.600 --> 00:28:40.030 align:middle line:90%
our spiritual values.

00:28:40.030 --> 00:28:43.390 align:middle line:84%
So in every moment of our
lives, one of these desires

00:28:43.390 --> 00:28:44.217 align:middle line:90%
is prominent.

00:28:44.217 --> 00:28:45.300 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: More prominent.

00:28:45.300 --> 00:28:50.160 align:middle line:84%
>> BECVAR: But they're all
functioning all the time

00:28:50.160 --> 00:28:50.960 align:middle line:90%
in our lives.

00:28:50.960 --> 00:28:55.120 align:middle line:84%
