So what you're talking
about rising signs

00:32:57.890 --> 00:32:59.275 align:middle line:84%
when you're looking
at compatibility.

00:32:59.275 --> 00:33:01.567 align:middle line:84%
>> BECVAR: Because the rising
sign has a lot to do with

00:33:01.567 --> 00:33:04.020 align:middle line:84%
the physical body and
how we occupy space,

00:33:04.020 --> 00:33:08.030 align:middle line:84%
so how well will I be able
to align with you in terms

00:33:08.030 --> 00:33:10.130 align:middle line:90%
of physical space?

00:33:10.130 --> 00:33:12.870 align:middle line:84%
Will there be some
complementarity there?

00:33:12.870 --> 00:33:16.190 align:middle line:84%
The moon sign is very important
in the Vedic tradition.

00:33:16.190 --> 00:33:17.960 align:middle line:84%
In India for thousands
of years, they've

00:33:17.960 --> 00:33:20.090 align:middle line:84%
arranged marriages
primarily based

00:33:20.090 --> 00:33:22.850 align:middle line:84%
on the moon signs, the
relationships of the moon signs.

00:33:22.850 --> 00:33:25.740 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: But
statistically, I mean,

00:33:25.740 --> 00:33:28.350 align:middle line:84%
it's a different culture where
you can't just easily divorce

00:33:28.350 --> 00:33:30.180 align:middle line:84%
and so forth, at
least in the past.

00:33:30.180 --> 00:33:33.630 align:middle line:84%
But statistically, if you
could even use that word,

00:33:33.630 --> 00:33:36.440 align:middle line:84%
didn't those relationships
also oftentimes have

00:33:36.440 --> 00:33:37.565 align:middle line:90%
some real staying power?

00:33:37.565 --> 00:33:41.090 align:middle line:84%
>> BECVAR: Yes, and I think part
of it is the culture really puts

00:33:41.090 --> 00:33:42.570 align:middle line:90%
a lot of importance on that.

00:33:42.570 --> 00:33:47.190 align:middle line:84%
